1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:02,878
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:03,003
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,631 --> 00:00:06,632
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,927 --> 00:00:10,928
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:12,638 --> 00:00:13,805
Adventure Time

6
00:00:13,889 --> 00:00:15,182
Come on, grab your friends

7
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,893
We'll go to very distant lands

8
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,270
with Jake the dog and Finn the human

9
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,772
The fun will never end

10
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,482
It's Adventure Time

11
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:36,161
JAKE: (PANTING) Remember last time
we were out this way?

12
00:00:37,204 --> 00:00:40,290
It was right after you messed things
all up with Flame Princess.

13
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,209
(CHUCKLES) Yeah, that sucked.

14
00:00:42,918 --> 00:00:44,586
But then we found
the Dungeon Train, remember?

15
00:00:44,962 --> 00:00:47,673
FINN: That was awesome.
JAKE: No. It wasn't.

16
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:50,842
Sure it was. Anyway, Flambo's brother's map

17
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:53,679
says the weird cave should be,
like, right over...

18
00:00:54,346 --> 00:00:56,848
Ah! It's right here.
(CHUCKLES) Come on, Jake.

19
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:59,601
Okay, hold on,
let me get out my sidewalk chalk.

20
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:01,979
I want to write all over the walls in there.

21
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:04,189
(ECHOING) What?
You can't use that stuff in here.

22
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:06,817
This is like an ancient, sacred temple.

23
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,572
Oh, well, now, that's just great.

24
00:01:12,531 --> 00:01:16,326
You don't put traps in the foyer!
The foyer is a safe space.

25
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:20,581
Man, not even Jake could smash
through this mess.

26
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:22,291
But maybe there's a back door or something.

27
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,043
Uh-oh! Options.

28
00:01:25,419 --> 00:01:27,462
Better leave a little trail in case I get lost.

29
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:29,715
Bread-crumb style. (CHUCKLES)

30
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:36,346
Plus, for if Jake gets in
and tries to track me down.

31
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:40,934
Too bad I don't still have that sidewalk...
Ow! (CRASHING)

32
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:42,686
(GROANS)

33
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:46,231
Okay, well, scratch that.

34
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:49,443
Now I really hope there's another way out.

35
00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:00,454
Hall of Egress.

36
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:02,247
Egress. Egress.

37
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:05,626
What's "egress" mean?

38
00:02:05,751 --> 00:02:06,710
"Exit."

39
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:09,421
Egress means exit.

40
00:02:10,422 --> 00:02:11,798
(GRUNTS)

41
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:14,551
(PANTING)

42
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,053
(SHUDDERS)

43
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:17,137
Okay.

44
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:18,680
(GRUNTING)

45
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,186
(SIGHS)

46
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:27,898
(GRUNTS)

47
00:02:31,318 --> 00:02:32,694
(SCREAMS)

48
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:39,326
Great. What am I supposed to do now?

49
00:02:40,327 --> 00:02:42,079
(INHALES DEEPLY AND SIGHS)

50
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:47,334
Wait.

51
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:49,961
Hey. Hey, I just smashed you.

52
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,171


53
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:52,839
Ah!

54
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,717
Magic door. Okay.

55
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:00,597
Right. But if I...

56
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:04,351
Ah?

57
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,978
Well done, Finn. You solved the magic door.

58
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:13,110
That ought to have done it. And...

59
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:17,364
Oh.

60
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:19,741
I guess this door's just too tricky for me.

61
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:21,368
Guess I better give up, right?

62
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:22,994
Wrong. Wrong!

63
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:24,705
Let's try that again.

64
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:30,252
Hmm.

65
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:33,255
It's smooth like metal.

66
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,219
Floor's smooth too.

67
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,139
Oh! What have we here?

68
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,015
An errant thread!

69
00:03:45,142 --> 00:03:46,143
(CHUCKLES)

70
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:48,228
It must lead back out.

71
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,522
Bread-crumb... Ooh!

72
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:51,982
Trap door?

73
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,735
(GRUNTS) Yow!

74
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:02,659
Spike trap.
Better head back and regroup.

75
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:04,786
Fiendish.

76
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:07,873
Anyway. Don't let's do that again.

77
00:04:16,131 --> 00:04:18,008
And right then straight.

78
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:20,510
And... Hey, now. Hold the phone.

79
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:22,137
There should be a left turn here.

80
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,097
Letters?

81
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:25,974
|IEII...

82
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,267
IIGII. ..

83
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,644
Egress! It spells "egress."

84
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:30,896
(CHUCKLES) This way!

85
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:34,399
And here's another one. And another.

86
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,400
(CHUCKLES)

87
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:37,402
- (TRAP DOOR OPENS)
- Whoa!

88
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,528
Oow!

89
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:42,616
Okay.

90
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:45,243
So, every map I make is wrong.

91
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:47,162
All the exit signs led to traps.

92
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:50,791
Plus the braille, the hieroglyphics,
and the tape recorder message too.

93
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:53,126
It's almost like the maze is
trying to tell me something.

94
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,129
Something confusing. Whatever!

95
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:58,799
Who needs you anyway, with your
stupid signs and messages?

96
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,675
I'm Finn Mertens, ya heard?

97
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:02,511
And I don't need no nothing!

98
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:04,387
Watch me. (INHALES DEEPLY)

99
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,056
(BABBLES)

100
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,897
(BABBLING SLOWLY)

101
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:17,317
(PANTING)

102
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:20,153
JAKE: Finn?

103
00:05:20,195 --> 00:05:21,530
Finn!

104
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,949
Jake! (LAUGHS) Jake, I'm coming!

105
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,326
Finn? Where are ya, buddy?

106
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:29,162
(GRUNTS) Jake!

107
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:32,457
(SUCKING TEETH)

108
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:36,086
That's a little disappointing. Still, though.
I'm in the homestretch here.

109
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:37,671
(BABBLES)

110
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:39,965
(GRUNTS) Jake!

111
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,592
Finn! Hey, there you are.

112
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:45,804
Yeah. Sorry to pop up,
then disappear again like that.

113
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:47,681
Again? You just got here, son.

114
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,225
I did? Shoot, man.

115
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,602
This cave has got me straight
scrambled up and down.

116
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:53,854
What cave?

117
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:57,065
What? Oh. Uh-oh.

118
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:00,944
- FINN: Well?
- Well, I followed your map,

119
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:02,863
but there's just a bunch of grass here.

120
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:04,114
What? Let me see!

121
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,243
Dang it. (BABBLES)

122
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:11,872
So, yeah. Everything I did to try
to make sense of the maze

123
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:13,707
or to play it safe totally backfired.

124
00:06:14,124 --> 00:06:16,877
But when I got fed up,
and started just charging in willy-nilly,

125
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:18,837
I was able to get to the end and find you.

126
00:06:19,129 --> 00:06:20,881
JAKE: And then the whole thing disappeared.

127
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:23,884
But I wonder how come I don't
remember any of it.

128
00:06:24,134 --> 00:06:27,137
I don't know.
I'm just hoping, maybe if I sleep it off,

129
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,388
maybe I'll be better in the morning.

130
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:31,391
Okay, well... Good night, buddy.

131
00:06:34,019 --> 00:06:35,729
Thanks, Jake. Good night.

132
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:39,149
BEEMO: Are you awake?

133
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:41,276
Yes.

134
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,111
Are you gonna open your eyes now?

135
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:45,030
Maybe.

136
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:46,156
Are you scared?

137
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,658
- No.
- Then do it.

138
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,161
(GULPS) On three.

139
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:52,996
BOTH: One, two,

140
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:54,539
three!

141
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:56,166
(SCREAMS)

142
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,420
JAKE: So, been almost a month now.

143
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:02,797
What do ya think?
You wanna try opening 'em?

144
00:07:03,048 --> 00:07:04,299
It's a beautiful day.

145
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:07,177
Plus, I need someone
to tell me if this hat looks cool.

146
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,553
Man, I told you...

147
00:07:10,055 --> 00:07:13,266
If I open 'em now, it'll just be the same.
I got to wait till something's different.

148
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:16,436
Yeah. That makes sense, I guess.

149
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:19,898
So, um, I got you a little something.

150
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:22,567
- A little present.
- Wow, thanks, man!

151
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:24,402
You're really gonna thank me.

152
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,071
- Gotcha!
- No!

153
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:29,074
FINN: Yeah, you've done it, like, 30 times now.

154
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:31,409
Ahhh! Ahhh!

155
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,411
Ahhh! Ahhh!

156
00:07:33,662 --> 00:07:35,914
It's like programmed
into your DNA or something.

157
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,791
(CHUCKLES) Well, shoot, man.

158
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:41,086
If I wanna do it that bad,
it must be kinda right, right?

159
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,338
- (SIGHS)
- Look at it from where I'm sitting.

160
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:46,216
All this funky pizzazz that only you can see,

161
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:48,969
that's like the literal
definition of a hallucination.

162
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:51,304
Either all that stuff is a dream,

163
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:54,307
or like, I'm a dream.
And I ain't no dream, ya heard?

164
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,226
Yeah, I know. I heard.

165
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,103
It's just that, well...

166
00:07:58,228 --> 00:07:59,980
- Hyah! Open up!
- (SCREAMS)

167
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:02,232
(SIGHS)

168
00:08:04,985 --> 00:08:06,111
Oh, Jake.

169
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:07,988
I know you mean well,

170
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:10,699
but I guess I got to see this
one through on my own.

171
00:08:16,621 --> 00:08:18,123
(SIGHS) I'll see you around, buddy.

172
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:22,752
(PANTING)

173
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:25,130
(GRUNTS)

174
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:27,007
Huh?

175
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:28,717
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

176
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:32,345
(SLURPING)

177
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:38,059
Huh? What the...

178
00:08:39,561 --> 00:08:40,520
(GASPS)

179
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:41,938
How long has this been going on?

180
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:43,440
CREYS)

181
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:46,317
Someone's apt to track me down,
bread-crumb style.

182
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:47,569
E.g. Jake.

183
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:49,070
Can't let him catch me.

184
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:51,823
No more threads to follow.

185
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,200
No more egress.

186
00:08:58,413 --> 00:08:59,706
(GRUNTING)

187
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,340
(SNORING)

188
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,468
(GNAWING)

189
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:13,094
(SPITS)

190
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,947
Mmm. It's cool in here.

191
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:34,866
Ain't nothing wrong with that.

192
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,368
Deep too. That's good.

193
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:41,372
Ain't nobody gonna be looking for me down...

194
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:42,373
Ugh!

195
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:45,460
(GASPS)

196
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:48,630
Egress! Egress! Egress! Egress!

197
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,104
BEEMO: Something's different.

198
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:14,155
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

199
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,251
(BIRDS CHIRP)

200
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,059
GIRL: Hurry, Finn.

201
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,311
At the seashell's center lies

202
00:10:45,687 --> 00:10:48,940
the cornucopia's smallest door.

203
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:07,959
Whoa! (LAUGHS)

204
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:09,586
That must have been some cave!

205
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:12,338
(LAUGHS) No comment!

206
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:18,178
Come along with me

207
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:22,974
And the butterflies and bees

208
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:28,229
This party is so crazy!

